        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2018-03-02T20:12:38Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Protecting Domestic Violence and Stalking Victims Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to:</p> <ul> <li> state that the term &quot;intimate partner&quot; includes a dating partner and any other person subject to a protection order under state domestic or family violence law; and</li> <li> expand the term &quot;misdemeanor crime of domestic violence&quot; to include the use or attempted use of physical force, or the threatened use of a deadly weapon, by a current or former intimate partner.</li> </ul> <p>The bill makes it a crime to knowingly sell or dispose of a firearm to a person who has been convicted of a misdemeanor crime of stalking. It also makes it a crime for such convicted stalker to receive or possess a firearm.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
